            <h2>Conjunctions</h2>
            <p><span class="initial-letter darkorange-text">C</span>onjunctions are words that join two words, phrases,
                clauses or sentences. In modern English, these are words like 'and', 'but', or 'because'. Conjunctions
                function exactly the same in Old English as they do in modern English, and do not take a case, number,
                or gender.
            </p>
            <p>Conjunctions are incredibly common, and can appear multiple times in a single sentence. For example,
                examine the sentence, '<em>Ac þeah ðu nu fier sie ðonne ðu wære, ne eart ðu eall of ðæm earde
                    adrifen ond ðu ðær on gedwolode- But though you are now farther than you were, you are not entirely
                    driven from the country, and you wandered therein</em>'.
