            <p>Most conjunctions are standalone words, and because they are so common you will often find many
                variations of spelling. For example, 'ond' in some dialects is spelled 'and', and '<em>for þy þe</em>',
                '<em>for þy</em>',
                '<em>for þæm þe</em>' and '<em>for þæm</em>' are all valid spellings for 'because', with some scribes
                alternating which version they use on the same page.</p>
            <div class="text-center padding-top">
                <table class="static-table table-striped inline-block">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Old<br>English</th>
                        <th>Modern<br>English</th>
                    </tr>
