                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>þeah</td>
                        <td>although</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p class="padding-top">Some conjunctions are found in pairs. This is true in modern English as well with
                phrases like
                'if...then', or 'either...or'. Examine the sentences, '<em>Gif hie nu gode sind, þonne wæron hie swa
                    gesceapene - If they now are good, then they were so created</em>' and '<em>Hie þa scipu eall oððe
                    tobracon oððe forbærndon - They either destroyed or burned all the
